Yeah good question. I imagine it should work like this:
```js
// stops the entire handler from having an effect
// event.stopPropagation() isn't called anyway
event.preventBaseUIHandler();

// *only* prevents event.stopPropagation() from being called
// but the logic still executes
event.preventBaseUIHandler({
  preventStopPropagation: true,
});
```

Are there any other configuration things to prevent?

Something like this came to my mind
```js
event.configure({
  dismissDialog: true,
  preventDefault: false,
  stopPropagation: false,
});
```

just spitballing though
